      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Constitutive model selection justified; contact formulation appropriate for titanium-on-UHMWPE interfaces.",
      "rationale": "Isotropic linear elasticity adopted for titanium alloy (Ti-6Al-4V) screw and rod; supported by stress levels well below yield in elastic regime. Augmented Lagrangian frictional contact (μ=0.2) used at screw-rod interface, consistent with published tribological data. Model form uncertainty estimated via comparison with nonlinear plasticity runs showing <2% QoI deviation in elastic range."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Material properties sourced from traceable coupon tests; geometric inputs from CMM measurements of physical constructs.",
      "rationale": "Elastic modulus (E=114 GPa) and Poisson ratio (ν=0.34) for Ti-6Al-4V derived from ASTM E8 tensile coupon tests on material from the same heat lot. Construct geometry digitized via coordinate measuring machine (CMM) with ±5 μm accuracy. Input uncertainty propagated through Monte Carlo sampling (5000 draws) as described in the UQ report (Section 4.3), which also includes a narrative screening sensitivity study identifying material modulus and screw-rod torque as the largest contributors to stiffness QoI variance; however, a formal structured sensitivity analysis has not been separately encoded in this credibility package."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "N≥10 constructs tested; sample traceability to production lot documented.",
      "rationale": "N=11 non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw constructs tested across two independent laboratories. All constructs sourced from a single production lot with full dimensional and material traceability. Inter-laboratory variability (CV=3.1%) within acceptable range. Gradation 3 achieved."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Test conditions span the range of clinically relevant loading scenarios; at minimum two distinct load configurations exercised.",
      "rationale": "Testing performed exclusively under ASTM F1717 standard compression-bending configuration at a single load angle. While this is the regulatory standard condition, only one test configuration was evaluated. Clinical loading includes combined torsion and lateral bending not captured here. Factor achieves Gradation 2; below required Gradation 3. This is the identified gap noted in the COU description."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Model boundary conditions and material inputs demonstrably equivalent to experimental setup; discrepancies quantified.",
      "rationale": "Boundary conditions in FEA replicate ASTM F1717 fixture geometry to within CMM measurement uncertainty. Applied displacement ramp rate and load cell compliance modeled explicitly. Material property equivalency confirmed by coupon test correlation. Residual assembly torque at screw-rod interface matched to torque-wrench calibration records (±0.1 N·m)."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Quantitative comparison metric (E/uval) computed for all QoIs; all values < 1.96.",
      "rationale": "E/uval computed for stiffness (1.31), yield force (1.54), and force at 40 mm (0.98). All three QoIs satisfy the pre-established acceptance criterion of E/uval < 1.96. Percentage differences (4.2%, 7.8%, 5.1%) all within 10% bound. Gradation 3 achieved."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoIs directly map to regulatory submission endpoints and clinical failure modes.",
      "rationale": "Construct stiffness, yield force, and force at 40 mm displacement are the three QoIs specified in ASTM F1717 and referenced in FDA guidance for spinal implant submissions. These quantities directly characterize clinically relevant failure modes (construct loosening, permanent deformation, fatigue initiation). QoI relevance fully established."
    },
